Package org.oucs.gaboto.exceptions

Contains various exceptions that are used in the Gaboto system.

See:
          Description

Exception Summary
CorruptDataException Is thrown when it is suspected that the data in Gaboto is corrupted.
CorruptTimeIndexException Is thrown when it is suspected the time index is corrupt.
EntityAlreadyExistsException Is thrown when an entity is added to the Gaboto model that already exists.
EntityClassNotFoundException Is thrown when the corresponding GabotoEntity class for an ontology type could not be determined.
EntityDoesNotExistException Is thrown when an GabotoEntity is accessed that does not exist in the model.
EntityPoolAmbiguousConfigurationException Is thrown if the GabotoEntityPoolConfiguration can be used for the creation of an GabotoEntityPool, but if it is ambiguous in some way.
EntityPoolInvalidConfigurationException Is thrown if an GabotoEntityPoolConfiguration is invalid.
GabotoException Provides a common base class for Exceptions within Gaboto.
GabotoRuntimeException Bas class for any runtime exception in the Gaboto system.
IllegalAnnotationException Is thrown if an GabotoEntity class is using annotations wrongly.
NoTimeIndexSetException Is thrown when a time index is accessed in an Gaboto model that did not create one.
PoolTransformationException  
QueryAlreadyPreparedException  
ResourceDoesNotExistException Is thrown when an RDF resource is accessed that does not exist.
UnsupportedFormatException Is thrown if an unsupported format is supplied.
 

Package org.oucs.gaboto.exceptions Description

Contains various exceptions that are used in the Gaboto system.
